  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Obstetrical blood loss is an important reason of maternal morbidity and mortality. Because of
      the increase in the rate of cesarean section, any procedure that could help reduce blood loss
      during cesarean section should be investigated. The purpose of this study was to compare 2
      methods of blunt expansion of the uterine incision at the time of cesarean delivery:
      transversal vs. cephalad-caudad.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
